<?xml version="1.0"?>
<rdf:RDF xmlns="http://www.semanticweb.org/vicki/ontologies/2025/9/untitled-ontology-90/"
     xml:base="http://www.semanticweb.org/vicki/ontologies/2025/9/untitled-ontology-90/"
     xmlns:owl="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
     xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
     xmlns:www="http://www.cair.za.net/"
     xmlns:xml="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"
     xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
     xmlns:cair="http://cair.za.net/"
     xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#"
     xmlns:terms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/"
     xmlns:defeasible="http://cair.za.net/defeasible#">
    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://victoriachama.org/net/MovieFilmOntology">
        <owl:versionIRI rdf:resource="http://victoriachama.org/net/MovieFilmOntology/1.0.0"/>
        <cair:consistent rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</cair:consistent>
        <terms:description xml:lang="en">This ontology models conceptual knowledge about movies and films with an emphasis on realistic, defeasible reasoning.  
Scope &amp; Purpose:
- Describes cinematic entities (Movie, Person, Studio, Genre, Rating, Award, DocumentaryStyle, AnimationTechnique, MovieSetting, MovieEndingType, MovieQuality, Budget categories, etc.), their relations (director, actor, genre, producer, distributor, adaptedFrom, isRemakeOf, hasAward, hasReview, etc.), and commonly used data properties (releaseDate, runtime, budget, boxOffice, ratings and scores).  
- Encodes *typical* domain patterns as defeasible axioms (for example: “Typically, a BlockbusterMovie has high box-office” or “Typically, an Indie has lower budget”), while allowing explicit exceptions (e.g., critically-acclaimed low-budget or cult classics). This supports non-monotonic inference where default conclusions can be overridden by higher-priority facts or exceptions.


Usage
This defeasible movie ontology provides a symbolic framework for reasoning about film metadata, genre–tone relationships, quality assessments, and exception-aware inferences intended for explainable classification and integration with film-data sources.</terms:description>
        <terms:license rdf:resource="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A defeasible ontology for movies and films that models genres, production roles, quality and recognition, narrative features, settings, and provenance-aware defeasible rules for typical but defeasible inferences about films (e.g., typical genre → expected tone, budget → box-office expectations).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Ontology>
    


